{
  "texts": [
    "I. INTRODUCTIONThe Cybercrime in Australia series [1] is intended to shed light on the victimisation and damages caused by cybercrime among computer users in Australia.",
    "The data originates from a survey conducted in early 2023, which included 13,887 individuals who use computers.",
    "Before the survey, 27% of participants reported encountering online abuse, 22% encountered malware, 20% faced stolen identities, and 8% fell victim to scams and fraud.",
    "Cybersecurity research encompasses a variety of domains, including authentication, software and hardware vulnerabilities, and defences against cyberattacks.",
    "However, only a small proportion of cybersecurity professionals have a complete comprehension of all facets of this industry."
  ]
}